{
  "article_id": "PlantersBanner1853",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "A "
      },
      {
        "text": "correspondent",
        "entity_key": "author_c",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " of the Newburyport Herald, witing [writing] from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", under date of September 11, 1853, relats [relates] the following singular incident:"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "We have now in ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbra",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "a great curiosity",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "—",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "an Indian woman",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " who has lived for eighteen years alone upon ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Island of San Nicholas",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a mall [small] island about 45 miles from ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this place",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", during which time she has not seen the face of a human being.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "This island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " was once peopled by "
      },
      {
        "text": "a tribe of Indians",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", to whom "
      },
      {
        "text": "the north-west tribes",
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_aleuts",
          "natam_kodiak"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " were hostile. To preserve "
      },
      {
        "text": "the remnant of this tribe",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " from destruction, as well as with a view to christianize them, "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Padres",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " induced them to come to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the main land",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "eighteen years ago. "
      },
      {
        "text": "After they were all on board ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " sent for them, ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this woman",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " swam ashore to look for ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which had been left; and a storm springing up in the night, ",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the vessel",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " was compelled to put to sea; on returning, she could not be found.",
        "tropes": [
          9
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " She was known to be alive by those who at times visited "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for the purpose of hunting otters, from the marks of fires and from foot-prints in the sand."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "On being approached the other day she manifested much joy which she betrayed by signs of the most significant character, and at once commenced packing up her few articles of furniture. Whether the sounds that she uttered are words or not has not yet been ascertained. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The man who found her",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " is familiar with five or six Indian languages, but he was unable to understand a single expression: it is more than probable that she has forgotten her native tongue entirely.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " Her clothing consists of skins of birds sewed together with the fibres of some tree or plant. Her food has been shell-fish, seals, and a small bulbous root, similar in appearance to an onion, but wholly tasteless."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The needles with which she stitched her garments are made of the sharp bones of a fish. She had two hooks made of a bent nail and sharpened by friction upon a stone. Her lines were beautifully twisted from the sinews of some animal, probably a species of fox which abounds on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Her age, as near as can be estimated, is about 55 or 60; her features are quite masculine; her hair of the color of dark brown, and very fine. This is very remarkable for an Indian; their hair, you know, is always jet black and coarse.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "In some future letter I will give you a more extended account of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this marvel of the 19th century",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". She is truly an object for the reflection of the philosopher and the inspection of the curious.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}